    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Julia\"><pre><span></span><code>    <span class=\"k\">for</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">pair</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">âˆˆ</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">enumerate</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">pairsâ€²</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span> <span class=\"n\">collect</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n        <span class=\"n\">Dâ‚</span><span class=\"p\">[[</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"n\">y</span><span class=\"p\">],</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"p\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">pair</span>\n        <span class=\"n\">tightnesses</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"p\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">somepurefunction</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Dâ‚</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n    <span class=\"k\">end</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>I don't see how this possibly could be parallelized. All threads will try to update the contents of <code>Dâ‚</code> and will overwrite each other in a data race. You will need to set things up so each thread has its own copy of <code>Dâ‚</code> to play with.</p>",
